did.unittitle: Resistencia Nicaragüense Ejército records
did.abstract: Reports, correspondence, memoranda, press releases, rosters, personnel records, statistics, financial records, and photographs relating to guerrilla military operations in Nicaragua, financing and supply of guerrilla forces, medical care and administration of justice in guerrilla-controlled areas, truce violations following the end of the war, and Nicaraguan refugees in Honduras. Includes records of the predecessor Fuerza Democrática Nicaragüense. Also on microfilm (136 reels).

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: Closed. Microfilm (Reels 1-44) of a portion of the collection available for use. Users must sign use agreement.

The Hoover Institution Archives only allows access to copies of audiovisual items, computer media, and digital files. To listen to sound recordings or to view videos, films, or digital files during your visit, please contact the Archives at least two working days before your arrival. We will then advise you of the accessibility of the material you wish to see or hear. Please note that not all material is immediately accessible.

userestrict.head: Publication Rights
userestrict.p: Users must sign use agreement. For copyright status, please contact the Hoover Institution Archives.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [Identification of item], Resistencia Nicaragüense Ejército records, [Box no.], Hoover Institution Archives.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Acquired by the Hoover Institution Archives in 1994.

accruals.head: Accruals
accruals.p: Materials may have been added to the collection since this finding aid was prepared. To determine if this has occurred, find the collection in Stanford University's online catalog at http://searchworks.stanford.edu/. Materials have been added to the collection if the number of boxes listed in the online catalog is larger than the number of boxes listed in this finding aid.

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: Nicaraguan resistance army engaged in guerrilla warfare against the Sandinista government of Nicaragua.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content of Collection
scopecontent.p: Reports, correspondence, memoranda, press releases, rosters, personnel records, statistics, financial records, and photographs relating to guerrilla military operations in Nicaragua, financing and supply of guerrilla forces, medical care and administration of justice in guerrilla-controlled areas, truce violations following the end of the war, and Nicaraguan refugees in Honduras. Includes records of the predecessor Fuerza Democrática Nicaragüense. Also on microfilm (136 reels).
Note: The following abbreviations are used throughout the list: C.R.: Comando Regional F.T.: Fuerza de Tarea
